Definition: the largest city and former capital of Turkey
Example: rebuilt on the site of ancient Byzantium by Constantine I in the fourth century; renamed Constantinople by Constantine who made it the capital of the Byzantine Empire; now the seat of the Eastern Orthodox Church
Synonyms: Stambul, Stamboul, Constantinople, city, i, Turkey, p, the, largest, and, former, capital, of, rebuilt, on, site, ancient, Byzantium, by, Constantine, I, in, fourth, century, renamed, who, made, it, Byzantine, Empire, now, seat, Eastern, Orthodox, Church
Category: noun.location
